Brazil has announced that it gave 7 days to Merck to lower the price
of its Efavirenz. If the company does not to so, Brazil will issue a
compulsory license. This decision was taken by President Lula and
confirmed by the Health Minister José Gomes Temporao. It was
published in the government publication listing acts and laws…
AFP dispatch below.
